WEBVTT

00:00:04.150 --> 00:00:07.670
{\an9}Special Week Wins Debut Race

00:00:07.190 --> 00:00:07.930
Hmm?

00:00:07.670 --> 00:00:10.780
{\an8}But She Freezes Pathetically…

00:00:08.450 --> 00:00:10.780
"But she freezes pathetically…"

00:00:12.260 --> 00:00:13.820
How cute.

00:00:13.820 --> 00:00:15.490
She looks good!

00:00:15.490 --> 00:00:17.180
I'm so embarrassed.

00:00:23.720 --> 00:00:28.940
Do you hear the fanfare as
we race towards the finish?

00:00:28.940 --> 00:00:35.470
I want to see that shining future with you

00:00:37.510 --> 00:00:43.810
{\an8}Umamusume

00:00:39.390 --> 00:00:43.680
{\an8}Pretty Derby

00:00:45.700 --> 00:00:51.420
If we just start to run, that's
where our story will begin

00:00:51.420 --> 00:00:56.440
It's always waiting right in front of us

00:00:56.440 --> 00:01:02.050
If you reach out just a little
more, we can seize that glory

00:01:02.050 --> 00:01:08.910
Aim for the top, challenge
them all, and it's off to the races

00:01:09.720 --> 00:01:14.910
Even the goddess of victory will be dazzled

00:01:14.910 --> 00:01:22.190
By your big debut that's just around the bend

00:01:22.190 --> 00:01:27.610
So can you hear the fanfare
as we race towards the finish?

00:01:27.610 --> 00:01:33.080
I want to see that shining future with you

00:01:33.080 --> 00:01:38.590
Let's overtake them all! It's
a track laid out just for you!

00:01:38.590 --> 00:01:46.350
Your dreams are at the finish if you believe

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:52.040
{\an8}Race 3

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:52.040
{\an8}First Big Win

00:01:52.040 --> 00:01:53.550
{\an8}Special Week

00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:55.800
Second win!

00:01:55.800 --> 00:01:57.050
{\an7}Vodka

00:01:56.300 --> 00:01:59.050
Pure skill!

00:01:59.050 --> 00:02:00.510
{\an9}Daiwa Scarlet

00:02:00.980 --> 00:02:02.890
An easy win!

00:02:02.890 --> 00:02:06.770
It's not so bad to try every once in a while.

00:02:02.890 --> 00:02:05.020
{\an9}Gold Ship

00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:11.270
{\an9}Silence Suzuka

00:02:13.730 --> 00:02:14.570
Can't make it!

00:02:15.350 --> 00:02:16.510
She crushed them.

00:02:16.510 --> 00:02:18.390
Eleven horse lengths between
her and second place…

00:02:18.390 --> 00:02:20.950
Her speed is the real deal.

00:02:20.950 --> 00:02:22.950
{\an8}Spica

00:02:25.470 --> 00:02:28.820
You guys are pretty good.

00:02:28.820 --> 00:02:30.350
Yeah!

00:02:31.750 --> 00:02:34.850
Vodka and Scarlet, you've both
won a match in the Juniors.

00:02:34.850 --> 00:02:36.050
Spe's got two wins.

00:02:36.050 --> 00:02:38.190
GolShi and Suzuka both have consecutive wins.

00:02:38.190 --> 00:02:42.640
At this rate, we'll catch up to
Hana's Team Rigil pretty soon.

00:02:42.640 --> 00:02:44.890
No problem at all.

00:02:44.890 --> 00:02:47.980
Your results out on the track aren't
the only thing on display, though.

00:02:47.980 --> 00:02:50.160
You mean people care about how cute we are?

00:02:50.160 --> 00:02:51.010
Look at this.

00:02:52.110 --> 00:02:53.150
You four, other than Shizuka…

00:02:53.540 --> 00:02:54.690
Get your concert down!

00:02:55.170 --> 00:02:59.400
Your win isn't perfect until you
have your Winning Concert down.

00:02:57.210 --> 00:02:59.400
{\an7}Team Spica

00:02:57.210 --> 00:02:59.400
{\an9}They win their races, but…
A train wreck follows.

00:02:59.400 --> 00:03:01.260
We can't help it!

00:03:01.260 --> 00:03:04.020
You're our trainer. You do
something about this.

00:03:04.020 --> 00:03:07.690
Well, it's true that it's partially my fault.
I focused too much on racing.

00:03:07.690 --> 00:03:09.410
So…

00:03:09.830 --> 00:03:11.080
{\an8}Karaoke Special Voucher

00:03:11.080 --> 00:03:12.260
Karaoke?

00:03:12.260 --> 00:03:13.650
Voucher?

00:03:13.650 --> 00:03:14.500
That's right.

00:03:14.500 --> 00:03:16.910
We're going to practice
your concerts, starting today.

00:03:17.500 --> 00:03:20.010
{\an8}Karaoke

00:03:17.500 --> 00:03:23.390
<i>Love's fireworks…</i>

00:03:20.850 --> 00:03:23.380
T-Teio!

00:03:23.380 --> 00:03:26.340
{\an8}Get in the game, and just do it.

00:03:23.390 --> 00:03:26.350
{\an6}Tokai Teio

00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:24.910
Teio-san?!

00:03:26.350 --> 00:03:27.640
<i>Tomorrow? Not happening.</i>

00:03:27.640 --> 00:03:30.810
<i>Let's "step it" right now.</i>

00:03:29.990 --> 00:03:31.890
{\an8}Wow.

00:03:31.890 --> 00:03:34.480
So this is the Teio Step
everyone's talking about.

00:03:34.480 --> 00:03:35.900
Pretty impressive.

00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:37.690
{\an8}Score

00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:39.360
{\an9}Page

00:03:35.900 --> 00:03:39.360
{\an6}"Love is a Derby"
Tokai Teio-san

00:03:37.780 --> 00:03:39.360
You guys are late!

00:03:39.360 --> 00:03:41.540
Why are you here, Teio?

00:03:41.540 --> 00:03:42.580
I asked her to come.

00:03:42.580 --> 00:03:43.500
What?

00:03:43.500 --> 00:03:45.460
She'll be teaching you how to sing and dance.

00:03:45.460 --> 00:03:46.910
You saw that just now, right?

00:03:47.270 --> 00:03:48.980
She's going to teach us?

00:03:48.980 --> 00:03:50.370
Yay!

00:03:50.370 --> 00:03:53.300
I fell in love with the way
she ran, and tried to scout her,

00:03:53.300 --> 00:03:55.600
but she wouldn't devote herself to the team.

00:03:55.600 --> 00:03:58.180
She said she'd teach you, though.

00:03:58.180 --> 00:04:02.000
The president told me to teach
you how to sing and dance, too.

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:03.130
The President?

00:04:03.180 --> 00:04:06.160
{\an8}Symboli Rudolf

00:04:03.620 --> 00:04:06.160
It's an embarrassment to this school
that there are some

00:04:06.160 --> 00:04:07.370
who can't perform a Winning Concert.

00:04:07.370 --> 00:04:07.850
So she said.

00:04:08.910 --> 00:04:10.430
But don't worry.

00:04:10.430 --> 00:04:13.560
We're gonna practice
'til you're ready to puke!

00:04:13.560 --> 00:04:15.810
What?!

00:04:18.210 --> 00:04:19.510
Are you okay?!

00:04:20.320 --> 00:04:22.860
Come on. Feel the rhythm.

00:04:22.860 --> 00:04:24.820
Okay, fine…

00:04:24.820 --> 00:04:26.930
Straight up here.

00:04:27.710 --> 00:04:29.330
Like this?

00:04:29.330 --> 00:04:31.020
Make sure you perform your steps right.

00:04:31.020 --> 00:04:33.240
What are you doing?

00:04:33.240 --> 00:04:33.830
Meditating.

00:04:35.830 --> 00:04:38.880
{\an8}Karaoke

00:04:39.470 --> 00:04:40.860
Thanks for today.

00:04:40.860 --> 00:04:42.220
Don't worry about it.

00:04:42.220 --> 00:04:43.830
It's nice that Teio-san taught us,

00:04:43.830 --> 00:04:46.840
so we can be sure we won't do anything
embarrassing during our concerts.

00:04:46.840 --> 00:04:49.300
If you join us, we'll take good care of you.

00:04:49.300 --> 00:04:50.760
Yeah…

00:04:50.760 --> 00:04:53.200
Teio has her own plans.

00:04:53.200 --> 00:04:57.790
I want an elite like Teio
to grow in her own way.

00:04:58.310 --> 00:05:00.960
Anyway, we're ready to win now.

00:05:00.960 --> 00:05:04.330
Special Week, become a
Triple Crown Horse Girl!

00:05:04.330 --> 00:05:05.610
What?!

00:05:05.930 --> 00:05:11.370
You're the only girl that can try to get
a Triple Crown on our team this year.

00:05:11.370 --> 00:05:14.230
You want me to be a Triple Crown girl?

00:05:14.230 --> 00:05:17.250
You've won two races so far,
so it only makes sense.

00:05:17.250 --> 00:05:19.740
What's your goal, again?

00:05:19.740 --> 00:05:21.010
Well…

00:05:21.010 --> 00:05:23.020
To become the best horse girl in Japan…

00:05:23.020 --> 00:05:23.670
Right?

00:05:23.670 --> 00:05:26.630
The Satsukishou, Japan Derby,
and the Kikkashou.

00:05:26.630 --> 00:05:27.970
Winning these three races

00:05:27.970 --> 00:05:31.570
is the fastest way to becoming
the best horse girl in Japan.

00:05:31.570 --> 00:05:33.580
A Triple Crown Horse Girl…

00:05:37.460 --> 00:05:39.580
Suzuka-san, I…

00:05:39.580 --> 00:05:43.390
If you have a chance to
do it, why not go for it?

00:05:43.390 --> 00:05:44.610
Go for it?

00:05:44.610 --> 00:05:45.850
In order for you to do that,

00:05:45.850 --> 00:05:48.830
you need to win the Satsukishou's
preliminary race, the Yayoishou.

00:05:48.830 --> 00:05:50.490
R-Right!

00:05:50.490 --> 00:05:52.830
You can do it!

00:05:50.490 --> 00:05:53.430
{\an8}Spe-senpai, go for it!

00:05:53.430 --> 00:05:54.650
We're rooting for you!

00:05:55.580 --> 00:05:57.290
{\an8}Class C

00:05:56.780 --> 00:05:59.960
Wh-Why do you look like that?

00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:03.050
I couldn't sleep because I was
worried about my next race.

00:06:03.050 --> 00:06:06.930
I've only really gotten lucky
with my wins so far.

00:06:03.610 --> 00:06:07.240
{\an9}Grass Wonder

00:06:09.060 --> 00:06:12.140
I've hurt my leg.

00:06:13.640 --> 00:06:16.250
You know, if you consider yourself lucky

00:06:16.250 --> 00:06:19.140
just to be able to get out there
on the track, you'll feel better.

00:06:20.500 --> 00:06:21.170
Yeah!

00:06:21.170 --> 00:06:23.490
I'm going to try my best out
there for the Yayoishou!

00:06:23.490 --> 00:06:25.190
Me, too.

00:06:25.780 --> 00:06:27.530
Seiun Sky-san!

00:06:25.780 --> 00:06:28.760
{\an7}Seiun Sky

00:06:27.530 --> 00:06:30.500
I'm not doing well, though.

00:06:30.500 --> 00:06:33.240
I hope things work out next time, but…

00:06:33.240 --> 00:06:35.780
She's had two wins in a row.

00:06:35.780 --> 00:06:40.290
Also, King Halo-san has had three
wins in a row since her debut.

00:06:40.730 --> 00:06:42.940
I-I'll try my best…

00:06:47.010 --> 00:06:49.630
The Nakayama Race Track is
a 2,000 meter turf track.

00:06:49.630 --> 00:06:52.890
{\an8}Yayoishou: 2000 meters

00:06:49.630 --> 00:06:52.890
{\an5}Goal - Hill - Start

00:06:50.050 --> 00:06:52.890
The next Yayoishou is the first
race for the Triple Crown.

00:06:52.890 --> 00:06:55.870
It has the same conditions
as the Satsukishou.

00:06:55.870 --> 00:06:57.960
So you can basically assume that how you do

00:06:57.960 --> 00:07:00.300
in the Yayoishou will tell you
how you'll do in the Satsukishou.

00:07:00.300 --> 00:07:01.520
Right.

00:07:01.520 --> 00:07:03.340
You're going to start from here.

00:07:03.340 --> 00:07:07.190
Take a loop around, and here's the goal.

00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:11.110
{\an7}Goal

00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:11.110
{\an8}Hill

00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:11.110
{\an9}Start

00:07:07.190 --> 00:07:11.110
But the problem is this soul-killing
hill in the last 200 meters.

00:07:11.110 --> 00:07:12.220
A hill…

00:07:12.220 --> 00:07:13.970
Many lose their momentum here on the hill,

00:07:13.970 --> 00:07:16.460
even if they've done well
up until that point.

00:07:16.460 --> 00:07:18.830
So it's a battle of endurance, then?

00:07:18.830 --> 00:07:21.840
These are going to be the longest
2,000 meters you'll have run so far.

00:07:21.840 --> 00:07:24.400
The finish is going to show your willpower.

00:07:24.400 --> 00:07:25.460
Willpower?

00:07:25.460 --> 00:07:31.140
And you need to watch out
for Seiun Sky the most.

00:07:32.090 --> 00:07:35.020
<i>She has three wins since
her debut for a reason!</i>

00:07:35.020 --> 00:07:38.100
<i>The most popular girl here, King Halo,
is standing before the gate!</i>

00:07:38.100 --> 00:07:41.940
I'll show you how a King runs.

00:07:38.100 --> 00:07:41.290
{\an9}King Halo

00:07:41.940 --> 00:07:44.470
She's still in good form
from her previous races.

00:07:45.220 --> 00:07:48.180
And we've got the third favorite,
Seiun Sky, standing before the gates.

00:07:48.180 --> 00:07:53.410
I know everyone's counting on me, but I'm
going to be as laid back as always.

00:07:53.410 --> 00:07:56.300
I don't understand her personality.

00:07:56.300 --> 00:07:57.120
I know.

00:07:57.120 --> 00:08:00.360
<i>And we have Number 13 on the far end,
the second favorite, Special Week.</i>

00:08:00.360 --> 00:08:01.540
<i>She's the last before the gates.</i>

00:08:02.210 --> 00:08:04.270
<i>This race will lead into the Satsukishou.</i>

00:08:08.470 --> 00:08:10.170
You sure are popular.

00:08:10.890 --> 00:08:13.580
P-Please don't tease me.

00:08:15.020 --> 00:08:17.000
<i>I need to challenge myself.</i>

00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:18.610
<i>I have to do what I can.</i>

00:08:19.390 --> 00:08:20.570
<i>And they're off!</i>

00:08:20.570 --> 00:08:21.890
<i>The start of the G-II, the Yayoishou!</i>

00:08:21.890 --> 00:08:23.820
<i>All the horse girls here
are trying for the Classic,</i>

00:08:23.820 --> 00:08:26.170
<i>running the Nakayama's 2,000 meters!</i>

00:08:26.860 --> 00:08:28.570
<i>All those people cheering us on…</i>

00:08:31.340 --> 00:08:32.360
<i>She's so fast!</i>

00:08:33.350 --> 00:08:35.110
<i>She's not laid back at all!</i>

00:08:35.110 --> 00:08:37.260
<i>Seiun Sky's pulling ahead!</i>

00:08:37.260 --> 00:08:38.600
<i>She's about three horse lengths ahead,</i>

00:08:38.600 --> 00:08:40.240
<i>and Tanshou Lupin follows in second.</i>

00:08:41.750 --> 00:08:44.160
Seiun Sky's getting far ahead.

00:08:44.160 --> 00:08:46.120
Don't lose your pacing!

00:08:46.120 --> 00:08:48.590
I wonder if Spe-senpai will be
okay keeping that position.

00:08:48.590 --> 00:08:51.150
The real challenge begins after the 4th turn.

00:08:53.310 --> 00:08:55.510
You can do it, Spe-chan.

00:08:56.010 --> 00:09:00.010
{\an4}Umamusume

00:08:56.010 --> 00:09:00.010
{\an4}Pretty Derby

00:09:05.190 --> 00:09:06.440
<i>A little further ahead…</i>

00:09:07.660 --> 00:09:09.360
We have someone coming
in from the outside.

00:09:09.930 --> 00:09:12.690
<i>Number 13, Special Week, has come
out front in the corner.</i>

00:09:13.050 --> 00:09:15.200
<i>It's a straight shot out of the 4th turn.</i>

00:09:15.200 --> 00:09:16.780
<i>Seiun Sky is in the lead.</i>

00:09:16.780 --> 00:09:19.950
<i>Tanshou Lupin is in second.
She looks a bit tired!</i>

00:09:19.950 --> 00:09:21.160
It's a straight shot from here!

00:09:21.160 --> 00:09:21.790
You can do it!

00:09:29.660 --> 00:09:31.800
<i>This is the soul-draining hill…</i>

00:09:31.800 --> 00:09:34.300
<i>But I still have my wind.</i>

00:09:34.300 --> 00:09:35.140
<i>This is it!</i>

00:09:36.710 --> 00:09:40.390
Make it up, make it up,
make it up, make it up!

00:09:40.390 --> 00:09:41.990
<i>I can't do it!</i>

00:09:44.770 --> 00:09:46.500
<i>I'm not catching up…</i>

00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:48.770
<i>But I still have a chance after the hill.</i>

00:09:48.770 --> 00:09:50.660
<i>Less than 100 meters left now!</i>

00:09:50.660 --> 00:09:52.440
<i>Seiun Sky is in the lead.</i>

00:09:52.440 --> 00:09:53.940
<i>Has she tired herself out?</i>

00:09:58.140 --> 00:10:01.070
<i>Special Week is closing in at
a ferocious pace from behind!</i>

00:10:07.780 --> 00:10:09.830
<i>If I can just get a bit further ahead…</i>

00:10:10.550 --> 00:10:13.050
<i>Special Week is closing in!</i>

00:10:13.050 --> 00:10:14.410
<i>They're neck and neck!</i>

00:10:15.740 --> 00:10:17.250
<i>She's pulled ahead!</i>

00:10:17.250 --> 00:10:19.470
You can do it!

00:10:20.590 --> 00:10:25.100
<i>Special Week finishes!</i>

00:10:32.380 --> 00:10:33.410
Yay!

00:10:33.410 --> 00:10:35.280
That hill scared me.

00:10:38.360 --> 00:10:41.820
Her ability to push ahead right
before the goal is godlike.

00:10:41.820 --> 00:10:44.870
She might really be able
to make Triple Crown…

00:10:45.270 --> 00:10:45.990
Huh?

00:10:47.450 --> 00:10:49.060
Congratulation.

00:10:47.940 --> 00:10:49.700
{\an8}Good job!

00:10:50.580 --> 00:10:51.880
We're having a victory party tonight!

00:10:57.150 --> 00:10:59.090
<i>How nice…</i>

00:11:06.250 --> 00:11:07.930
<i>I see.</i>

00:11:11.530 --> 00:11:15.760
Special Week, congratulations
on your big Yayoishou win!

00:11:15.760 --> 00:11:18.530
Cheers!

00:11:18.530 --> 00:11:20.320
Thank you.

00:11:18.530 --> 00:11:22.030
{\an8}Special Week G-II Yayoishou
Big Win!!

00:11:20.320 --> 00:11:21.280
That was so cool.

00:11:21.280 --> 00:11:23.450
Congratulations!

00:11:28.620 --> 00:11:31.020
That Nakayama hill is tough, huh?

00:11:31.020 --> 00:11:33.830
Yeah, it felt like a wall.

00:11:34.630 --> 00:11:37.030
Your Winning Concert was cute.

00:11:37.030 --> 00:11:38.810
Really? I'm glad you said that.

00:11:38.810 --> 00:11:41.090
Yeah, it's gotten a lot better.

00:11:41.090 --> 00:11:45.110
<i>Running straight toward you…</i>

00:11:45.110 --> 00:11:48.100
<i>Dreams and hopes…</i>

00:11:48.490 --> 00:11:50.300
Teio really helped me out.

00:11:50.300 --> 00:11:52.190
Show me how to dance better
the next chance you get.

00:11:52.190 --> 00:11:52.980
Sure.

00:11:52.980 --> 00:11:54.890
R-Really?

00:11:54.890 --> 00:11:55.690
Yep.

00:11:55.690 --> 00:11:58.690
I've decided to join Spica, anyway.

00:12:00.310 --> 00:12:01.910
What?!

00:12:02.530 --> 00:12:03.480
What?!

00:12:03.480 --> 00:12:04.950
You're surprised, too?!

00:12:07.220 --> 00:12:09.410
{\an8}Student Council President

00:12:07.980 --> 00:12:09.410
You're joining Spica?

00:12:09.720 --> 00:12:10.870
Yes.

00:12:10.870 --> 00:12:12.950
You don't want to be in Rigil?

00:12:12.950 --> 00:12:15.040
I gave it a lot of thought,

00:12:15.040 --> 00:12:17.860
but I'd rather have fun.

00:12:20.950 --> 00:12:24.290
You said you wanted to be like me, right?

00:12:24.290 --> 00:12:24.990
Yeah.

00:12:24.990 --> 00:12:27.760
My goal is to get the Triple Crown!

00:12:28.620 --> 00:12:30.880
Just having fun isn't enough,

00:12:30.880 --> 00:12:33.140
if you have a goal you want to achieve.

00:12:33.980 --> 00:12:37.730
You know what I'm going
to say next, right, Teio?

00:12:37.730 --> 00:12:39.150
Yes.

00:12:40.890 --> 00:12:42.690
Once you get stronger, let's run together.

00:12:42.690 --> 00:12:43.620
Yeah.

00:12:44.630 --> 00:12:47.120
It's a promise. Don't forget.

00:12:47.120 --> 00:12:48.010
Yeah.

00:12:48.830 --> 00:12:51.920
I want to catch up to the president.

00:12:51.920 --> 00:12:53.580
That's why I'm going to get better in Spica,

00:12:53.580 --> 00:12:55.710
and try racing with the president.

00:12:56.820 --> 00:12:59.190
That's a big goal. Sounds good to me.

00:12:59.190 --> 00:12:59.800
Yep!

00:13:00.150 --> 00:13:02.260
Let's do this, everyone.

00:13:03.510 --> 00:13:05.220
Welcome.

00:13:05.220 --> 00:13:05.980
Yeah, welcome.

00:13:05.980 --> 00:13:07.860
Welcome.

00:13:07.860 --> 00:13:08.620
Yep.

00:13:08.620 --> 00:13:10.510
Time to eat!

00:13:17.940 --> 00:13:21.440
{\an9}Air Groove

00:13:18.310 --> 00:13:21.440
President, you're still here.

00:13:22.070 --> 00:13:23.780
Want to have a drink with me?

00:13:23.780 --> 00:13:25.650
S-Sure.

00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:33.074
