00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:53.560
{\an8}Satsukishou

00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:53.560
{\an9}Turf

00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:53.560
{\an6}Special Week
LT Nice Guy
Sanyo Holy
Clark Arthur
Yasuda Repeat
Massive Koutei
King Halo

00:13:54.420 --> 00:13:56.060
Hey, Hana.

00:13:56.060 --> 00:13:57.560
Is this a new brand of coffee?

00:14:02.410 --> 00:14:04.210
Playing a game?

00:14:04.210 --> 00:14:05.130
Is it any good?

00:14:06.990 --> 00:14:10.340
Hey, why aren't you going to
use her for the Satsukishou?

00:14:10.810 --> 00:14:14.700
I guess I'm invisible to you.

00:14:14.700 --> 00:14:18.170
Hey, why did you come back?

00:14:20.460 --> 00:14:24.210
I couldn't give up on my dream so easily.

00:14:24.210 --> 00:14:26.660
I thought that was the case.

00:14:26.660 --> 00:14:29.260
Then you should be working
a lot harder, shouldn't you?

00:14:29.260 --> 00:14:31.320
I believe in laissez-faire.

00:14:31.320 --> 00:14:35.460
Their ability to make their own decisions
during a race is the most important.

00:14:35.460 --> 00:14:38.480
You're going to have problems
if you believe that.

00:14:38.480 --> 00:14:43.980
{\an7}Satsukishou Competitors
Announced!

00:14:38.480 --> 00:14:43.980
{\an4}Special Week wins Yayoishou
Will she make the G-I race?!

00:14:38.480 --> 00:14:43.980
{\an5}King Halo Ready to go!

00:14:38.480 --> 00:14:43.980
{\an8}Horse Girl Daily

00:14:38.980 --> 00:14:41.730
The next race your favorite
girl is going to be in…

00:14:42.210 --> 00:14:43.980
I think it'll be hard for her.

00:14:46.020 --> 00:14:48.450
Even if things don't
turn out the way we want,

00:14:48.450 --> 00:14:52.470
it'll be up to her whether or not she
picks herself up from there.

00:15:04.850 --> 00:15:08.210
What did the letter from your mom say?

00:15:08.590 --> 00:15:11.610
She said she wanted to come see me race.

00:15:11.610 --> 00:15:13.620
I want her to come too,

00:15:13.620 --> 00:15:16.850
but I'm going to tell her it's okay if
she doesn't, because it'll cost a lot.

00:15:17.830 --> 00:15:20.230
Here you are. I've tightened them up nice.

00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:22.810
Oh, thank you.

00:15:23.300 --> 00:15:25.020
I hope you win
the next one, too.

00:15:25.690 --> 00:15:27.550
I'll do my best!

00:15:28.250 --> 00:15:30.650
<i>Watch me on TV, Mom.</i>

00:15:30.650 --> 00:15:32.240
<i>I'm going to win!</i>

00:15:37.450 --> 00:15:40.380
It's the Satsukishou tomorrow.

00:15:40.380 --> 00:15:40.960
Right!

00:15:41.330 --> 00:15:43.650
A G-I race is one of
the most prestigious races.

00:15:43.650 --> 00:15:47.310
You run in your best clothes for this.

00:15:47.310 --> 00:15:48.510
These were special ordered.

00:15:48.510 --> 00:15:49.690
Try them on.

00:15:52.150 --> 00:15:54.220
J-Just for me?

00:15:54.710 --> 00:15:56.140
Thank you!

00:15:56.140 --> 00:15:58.020
Lucky…

00:15:58.670 --> 00:16:00.500
Now hurry up, and get changed.

00:16:00.500 --> 00:16:01.730
You get out of here.

00:16:07.900 --> 00:16:08.880
That looks good!

00:16:08.880 --> 00:16:09.960
Lucky…

00:16:09.960 --> 00:16:11.540
Looks good on you.

00:16:11.540 --> 00:16:13.030
Clothes make the girl.

00:16:13.030 --> 00:16:14.820
Thank you.

00:16:14.820 --> 00:16:16.330
I really appreciate it.

00:16:18.970 --> 00:16:19.870
What's wrong?

00:16:19.870 --> 00:16:22.830
N-Nothing. It's nothing.

00:16:33.300 --> 00:16:35.680
{\an8}Satsukishou

00:16:37.750 --> 00:16:40.310
<i>And the last to make her
appearance is the favorite…</i>

00:16:40.310 --> 00:16:43.820
<i>Bracket 8, Number 18, Special Week!</i>

00:17:01.700 --> 00:17:03.820
<i>The audience is even louder than last time.</i>

00:17:03.820 --> 00:17:05.350
<i>This is a G-I.</i>

00:17:05.870 --> 00:17:10.450
<i>She's wearing an adorable,
white and purple uniform-style outfit.</i>

00:17:10.450 --> 00:17:12.510
<i>She looks like she's in good condition, too.</i>

00:17:16.010 --> 00:17:17.660
<i>What is she doing?</i>

00:17:27.480 --> 00:17:28.860
<i>The G-I Satsukishou…</i>

00:17:28.860 --> 00:17:33.820
<i>Which horse girl will clear the
first hurdle to the Triple Crown?</i>

00:17:34.190 --> 00:17:37.610
<i>I'm feeling decent, and I'm
starting from the outside again.</i>

00:17:38.220 --> 00:17:40.940
<i>Mom, I'm going to win.</i>

00:17:43.110 --> 00:17:44.190
<i>And they're off!</i>

00:17:44.190 --> 00:17:47.080
<i>They're all out of the gates just fine.</i>

00:17:47.530 --> 00:17:50.540
<i>Number 2, Kokuei Number One,
has jumped in front.</i>

00:17:50.540 --> 00:17:52.840
<i>King Halo is pulling ahead.</i>

00:17:52.840 --> 00:17:55.940
<i>I just have to run like I did before.</i>

00:17:55.940 --> 00:17:57.840
<i>I'm good in this position for now.</i>

00:17:57.840 --> 00:17:59.760
<i>Yes, that's right.</i>

00:17:59.760 --> 00:18:01.470
<i>Don't get started just yet.</i>

00:18:03.470 --> 00:18:06.730
<i>On the other side, Kokuei Number
One remains in the lead,</i>

00:18:06.730 --> 00:18:08.520
<i>followed by Halcyon.</i>

00:18:08.520 --> 00:18:11.190
<i>King Halo is in third,
a good position for her.</i>

00:18:11.550 --> 00:18:14.450
<i>The favorite, Special Week,
is in a pack in the rear.</i>

00:18:14.450 --> 00:18:16.210
<i>She's waiting for her chance to pounce.</i>

00:18:16.210 --> 00:18:18.930
Feels like it'll be the
same as the Yayoishou.

00:18:18.930 --> 00:18:21.700
So she'll try to win in the
straightaway after the hill, right?

00:18:21.700 --> 00:18:24.200
Yeah, I wonder if we'll get to
see her race to catch up again!

00:18:24.200 --> 00:18:26.700
<i>They've hit the third turn.
Only 600 meters left.</i>

00:18:26.700 --> 00:18:29.230
<i>Special Week is coming up from the outside.</i>

00:18:29.230 --> 00:18:30.650
<i>Will she make her move all the way up front?</i>

00:18:30.650 --> 00:18:32.210
<i>She's entering the fourth turn!</i>

00:18:32.210 --> 00:18:34.430
<i>I started around here last time.</i>

00:18:34.430 --> 00:18:36.060
<i>It's about time!</i>

00:18:36.060 --> 00:18:37.300
<i>Here I go!</i>

00:18:38.970 --> 00:18:40.420
What?!

00:18:40.420 --> 00:18:41.720
When did she…

00:18:41.720 --> 00:18:45.430
<i>Seiun Sky has started to pull ahead!</i>

00:18:45.430 --> 00:18:46.590
<i>She's fast.</i>

00:18:46.590 --> 00:18:47.890
<i>I need to catch up.</i>

00:18:47.890 --> 00:18:48.810
<i>I gotta do this!</i>

00:18:48.810 --> 00:18:49.960
<i>Almost there!</i>

00:18:49.960 --> 00:18:51.190
<i>Get up there!</i>

00:18:53.580 --> 00:18:56.190
<i>I can't!</i>

00:18:58.390 --> 00:19:01.530
<i>I can't!</i>

00:19:02.180 --> 00:19:03.860
<i>I can't close the gap.</i>

00:19:07.300 --> 00:19:08.290
<i>It's okay.</i>

00:19:08.290 --> 00:19:10.920
<i>She can handle the straight after the hill.</i>

00:19:11.280 --> 00:19:13.420
<i>Do it. That's the place.</i>

00:19:17.370 --> 00:19:18.620
<i>This is it.</i>

00:19:21.380 --> 00:19:23.420
<i>Why can't I catch up?</i>

00:19:30.620 --> 00:19:31.600
<i>Why?</i>

00:19:31.600 --> 00:19:33.350
Just as I thought.

00:19:35.360 --> 00:19:37.890
<i>Seiun Sky's keeping her lead.</i>

00:19:37.890 --> 00:19:39.740
<i>And she's across the finish line!</i>

00:19:39.740 --> 00:19:41.490
<i>King Halo comes in second.</i>

00:19:41.490 --> 00:19:44.240
<i>Special Week only comes in third!</i>

00:19:44.240 --> 00:19:47.460
Seiun Sky kept up her pace at the end.

00:19:47.460 --> 00:19:49.750
Seiun Sky won through strategy.

00:19:49.750 --> 00:19:52.730
<i>I feel bad for Special
Week not coming in first.</i>

00:20:00.570 --> 00:20:03.470
Congratulations, Seiun Sky!

00:20:04.770 --> 00:20:06.970
Congratulations!

00:20:09.380 --> 00:20:12.480
<i>I won…</i>

00:20:12.820 --> 00:20:14.670
Thank you!

00:20:28.430 --> 00:20:32.070
Suzuka-san, thank you for
cheering me on today.

00:20:32.070 --> 00:20:32.960
Yeah…

00:20:33.450 --> 00:20:35.340
Too bad about today.

00:20:35.340 --> 00:20:37.720
I was so close.

00:20:37.720 --> 00:20:38.670
Yeah.

00:20:38.670 --> 00:20:41.300
I can just try harder next time.

00:20:41.300 --> 00:20:42.110
Yeah.

00:20:42.110 --> 00:20:44.630
I'm going to win next time!

00:20:47.460 --> 00:20:48.640
Oh…

00:20:49.050 --> 00:20:50.280
What is it?

00:20:50.280 --> 00:20:52.620
I forgot something.

00:20:52.620 --> 00:20:54.210
You go ahead home.

00:20:54.210 --> 00:20:54.610
Huh?

00:20:54.610 --> 00:20:55.900
See you.

00:21:14.410 --> 00:21:17.330
I ran like I did in the Yayoishou!

00:21:17.330 --> 00:21:21.050
I wanted my mom to watch me win.

00:21:21.650 --> 00:21:25.030
I was so arrogant!

00:21:25.030 --> 00:21:26.260
<i>Spe-chan…</i>

00:21:29.680 --> 00:21:31.670
T-Trainer-san…

00:21:32.430 --> 00:21:34.590
Wh-Why are you here?

00:21:40.650 --> 00:21:42.730
Damn it!

00:21:42.730 --> 00:21:45.030
I should have trained her better!

00:21:45.030 --> 00:21:47.530
Damn it!

00:21:48.180 --> 00:21:49.590
Trainer-san…

00:21:52.790 --> 00:21:54.650
How does it feel to lose?

00:21:55.870 --> 00:21:57.460
It's frustrating.

00:21:57.460 --> 00:21:58.530
I see.

00:21:59.500 --> 00:22:00.990
Then you have the Derby.

00:22:01.500 --> 00:22:02.840
The Derby?

00:22:02.840 --> 00:22:05.980
You're going to beat Seiun Sky
in the Japan Derby.

00:22:05.980 --> 00:22:08.090
Use your loss to get stronger.

00:22:08.090 --> 00:22:08.950
Understood?

00:22:11.010 --> 00:22:11.850
Yes!

00:22:25.740 --> 00:22:28.810
In a dash, in a flash,
just a little more now,

00:22:28.810 --> 00:22:31.520
each new race like a dream neverending

00:22:31.520 --> 00:22:34.330
Every one of us will blaze a
trail aimed right for the stars

00:22:34.330 --> 00:22:39.500
Together we'll run! Let's
go! Our starting gate!

00:22:48.630 --> 00:22:53.960
With curiosity in hand, go tug
on tomorrow's tail and say hello

00:22:53.960 --> 00:22:58.960
It's right there, so go on and close
the gap now (Right here and now!)

00:22:59.670 --> 00:23:05.050
Can't play by the rules they tell
you! Gotta learn it all by experience!

00:23:05.050 --> 00:23:09.990
If we just plan to run for the
end, everything will turn out okay!

00:23:10.150 --> 00:23:14.020
Can't get me down,
hesitate, or go too slowly!

00:23:15.770 --> 00:23:19.740
We know that deep in our hearts is a song

00:23:19.820 --> 00:23:22.960
that sings "give it your all"! Make it shine!

00:23:23.540 --> 00:23:26.760
In a dash, in a flash, just a
little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:26.760 --> 00:23:29.510
every step like the wind
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:29.510 --> 00:23:32.410
A twinkling star that we wear
on our sleeves (But only one!)

00:23:32.410 --> 00:23:34.710
Let's let our hearts race
together as one! (Grow up! Shine!)

00:23:34.710 --> 00:23:37.840
One more step, one more push,
just a little more now, (Dash! Dash!)

00:23:37.840 --> 00:23:40.490
each new race like a dream
neverending (Zoom! Zoom!)

00:23:40.490 --> 00:23:43.340
Every one of us will see
our path to the very end!

00:23:43.340 --> 00:23:49.070
Let's run now, everyone!
Let's go! Our starting gate!

